The paper proposes a machine learning solution for Multi-view Multi-instance Multi-label Learning (M3L) which deals with complex objects represented with different feature views and annotated with multiple labels. This problem is related to several sub-fields of computer science such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, since the proposed solution is based on matrix factorization and collaborative filtering techniques, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LG.
